{
  "texts": [
    "RQ2 is one of the questions that most shaped our research.",
    "It was created to examine existing clinical research problems and specific blockchain solutions for these problems.",
    "RQ3 was constructed to reveal the evaluation process of clinical research.",
    "RQ4 was constructed to reveal other technologies used with blockchain technology.",
    "RQ5 was formulated to define the application of blockchain [10,25,26] Blockchain technology provides a robust solution by permanently recording all aspects and metadata of the research process, including protocols, hypotheses, analysis methods, and subject selection criteria, all with chronological timestamps Research subject/patient recruitment [21,27,28] Blockchain has the potential to aggregate all patient-related data, creating a holistic medical history accessible to investigators through a shared framework."
